_🩺 Stability & Availability_ | _🟠 Major_ | _⚡ Quick win_

**Save the distil cache before gold rendering to avoid wasting LLM calls on failure.**

If `buildGoldDocs` or `writeFileSync` (lines 112–124) throws, `saveDistilCache` at line 125 never executes. On the next run, all batches that were just distilled via LLM will be re-called because the cache wasn't persisted. Moving the cache save before gold rendering (or wrapping gold rendering in a try/finally) preserves the expensive LLM results.





<details>
<summary>🔧 Proposed fix: save cache before gold rendering</summary>

```diff
   const sourceDigests = toSourceDigests({ digests: run.digests, records })
   for (const digest of sourceDigests) {
     writeJsonFile({ path: join(silverDigestsDir({ home }), `${digest.source}.json`), value: digest })
   }

+  saveDistilCache({ cache, home })
+
   const index = readSilverIndex({ home })
   const docs = buildGoldDocs({
     people: index.people,
     containers: index.containers,
     sources: sourceDigests,
     opportunities: index.opportunities,
     builtAtIso: new Date().toISOString(),
   })
   for (const doc of docs) {
     const path = join(goldDir({ home }), doc.path)
     mkdirSync(dirname(path), { recursive: true })
     writeFileSync(path, doc.markdown, 'utf8')
   }
-  saveDistilCache({ cache, home })
```
</details>

